Events
--------
Event: display books
Event: add book book
Event: remove book


DOMContentLoaded 
--------------------
this event fires when  HTML document has been completely loaded and parsed.

eg: 
    document.addEvenListener('DOMContentLoaded', function());




checking whether an element contains a class
-------------------------
const getB = document.querySelector('.btn')
if (getB.classList.contains('btn'))
    { 
        console.log(true)
}else
{
    console.log(false)
}

here if button element has class btn then it is true.


removing parent of parent Elmeent
--------------------
getB.parentElement.parentElement.remove();


    // remove alert in 3secs. use setInterval()
    setInterval(()=> {
        document.querySelector('.alert').remove();
    }, 3000);


LocalStorage 
---------------
- to store the data persistent.
- store data as key:value pairs, so we pass data in form of object.
- but localstorage didnt accept object types
- so first have to stringify it to make string 
- and pass that string data to it.

methods
---------
LocalStorage.getItem();
    -to get an item from localstorage.

v get items as strings from LocalStorage. so have 
to parse it to json object using JSON.parse();


